						               													<description>Game description&amp;#10;The player who scores the most points, wins the game.&amp;#10;You can score points by eating your opponent's tokens (1 point each eaten token) or achieving a Connect 5 (5 points).&amp;#10;Once any player achieves Connect 5, the round is over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules&amp;#10;The player who, at the end of all rounds scores more points, wins the game.&amp;#10;If, during a round, none of the players scores a Connect 5 or if there are no more available free dots on the game board and it&amp;rsquo;s not possible to place or move any token, the round is over and the final score is calculated counting the tokens that have been eaten by each player.&amp;#10;To score Connect 5, a player must have 5 of his tokens placed on 5 consecutive dots on the game board, without any obstacle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The double board game&amp;#10;Connect 5 game board has 2 sides, one for basic games, one for advanced games!&amp;#10;The side labeled as &amp;ldquo;B&amp;rdquo; is the Basic game board.&amp;#10;It&amp;rsquo;s suitable for new players who want to gradually explore the game mechanics.&amp;#10;Nevertheless, the basic board offers a consistent challenge level also to more experienced players.&amp;#10;The side labeled as &amp;ldquo;A&amp;rdquo; is the Advanced game board and offers more challenging game paths presenting a harder challenge for the real Connect 5 champions!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
